## 4. Environment Configuration

All sensitive credentials are stored in [.env.local](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/.env.local) at the project root ([/eduforall/.env.local](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/.env.local)). This file is **never committed to version control**.

| Variable | Description | Example Value |
|---|---|---|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME` | Cloudinary cloud name (public, used in client code) | `windows2k63d` |
| `CLOUDINARY_API_KEY` | Cloudinary API key (server-only) | `691434492513835` |
| `CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET` | Cloudinary API secret (server-only) | `CxgFLsnE4e...` |
| `MONGODB_URI` | MongoDB Atlas connection string | `mongodb+srv://...` |
| `MONGODB_DB` | *(Optional)* Database name override | `admin-panel` |

> [!CAUTION]
> The `CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET` and `MONGODB_URI` contain credentials that grant full read/write access to both the image store and the database. These must be rotated immediately if accidentally committed to git or exposed publicly.

> [!WARNING]
> `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` prefixed variables are embedded into the browser JavaScript bundle and visible to all users. Only the `CLOUD_NAME`, which Cloudinary treats as non-secret, should have this prefix. The `API_KEY` and `API_SECRET` are correctly using non-public names.

