    APIRemoveQR --> Cloudinary

    APIContact --> MongoDB
    APIContactQueries --> MongoDB
    APIGetSettings --> MongoDB
    APISaveSettings --> MongoDB
```

### Rendering Strategy

All user-facing pages (`/`, `/about`, `/gallery`, `/contact`, `/donate`, `/admin`) are **Client Components** as indicated by the `'use client'` directive. They use `useEffect` to fetch data from API routes after the initial page render. This means:

- The initial HTML sent to the browser contains **no dynamic data** from Cloudinary or MongoDB.
- Images and settings appear only after client-side JavaScript runs.
- This creates a content layout shift (CLS) effect where images appear after load.

The root [layout.tsx](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/layout.tsx) is a **Server Component** that wraps all pages and injects the Navigation and Footer globally.

