## 6. Pages & User-Facing Routes

### 6.1 `/` — Home Page
**File:** [src/app/page.tsx](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/page.tsx)  
**Type:** Client Component  
**Purpose:** Landing page and primary call-to-action.

**Sections:**
1. **Hero Section** — Full-viewport background image (`hero.jpg`) with a 30% black overlay. Contains H1 headline with "Donate Now" and "Learn More" CTA buttons.
2. **Get Involved Section** — Grid of three cards: Volunteer, Donate, Partner. CTAs link to `/contact` and `/donate`.
3. **Mission Section** — Two-column layout: detailed long-form text on education in India (left, 2/3 width) + dynamic Cloudinary gallery image (right, 1/3 width).
4. **Our Programs Section** — Two-column layout: Cloudinary gallery image (left, 1/3) + numbered list of 6 programs.
5. **Full-Viewport Image Section** — 100vh background block using a third random Cloudinary image.

**Behavior:** On mount, fetches `/api/gallery-list` and randomly selects 3 unique images for placement across sections. Uses a while-loop deduplication algorithm to ensure unique indices.

---

### 6.2 `/about` — About Us
**File:** [src/app/about/page.tsx](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/about/page.tsx)  
**Type:** Client Component  
**Purpose:** Organisation mission, founding story, programs, and volunteer CTA.

**Sections:**
1. **Main Lead** — Drop-cap intro paragraph + Cloudinary image (col-span-2 of 5).
2. **How We Began / What We Do** — Two-column editorial grid.
3. **Emotional Learning / Play & Expression** — Two-column editorial grid.
4. **Two inline Cloudinary images** — Displayed in a 2-column grid.
5. **Looking Ahead** — Vision statement section.
6. **Volunteer CTA** — Three action buttons linking to `/contact` and `/donate`.

**Behavior:** Fetches `/api/gallery-list`, shuffles the result array, and selects the first 3 for display across the page.

---

### 6.3 `/gallery` — Photo Gallery
**File:** [src/app/gallery/page.tsx](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/gallery/page.tsx)  
**Type:** Client Component  
**Purpose:** Masonry-style photo grid with full-screen modal viewer.

**Layout:** CSS columns (`columns-1 sm:columns-2 md:columns-3 lg:columns-4`) with `break-inside-avoid` to create a Pinterest-style masonry flow.

**Features:**
- Lazy loading with `loading="lazy"` on all gallery images.
- `quality={60}` for thumbnails to reduce bandwidth.
- Click-to-expand modal: clicking any image opens a full-screen overlay with the image displayed at `quality={70}`.
- Modal dismisses on clicking the background overlay or the × button.

**Behavior:** Fetches entire `/api/gallery-list` (up to 100 images) on mount and renders all of them.

---

### 6.4 `/contact` — Contact Form
**File:** [src/app/contact/page.tsx](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/contact/page.tsx)  
**Type:** Client Component  
**Purpose:** Intake form for volunteers, partners, and general inquiries.

**Form Fields:**
| Field | Type | Validation | Options |
|---|---|---|---|
| Full Name | `text` | Required (HTML5) | — |
| Phone Number | `tel` | Required (HTML5) | — |
| Subject | `select` | Required (HTML5) | General Inquiry, Volunteer Opportunities, Partnership Opportunities, Feedback |
| Message | `textarea` | Required (HTML5) | 4 rows |

**Submission:** `POST /api/contact` with `Content-Type: application/json`. On success, shows `alert()` and resets the form. On failure, shows error `alert()`.

**Layout:** Two-column (`2/3 form + 1/3 random Cloudinary gallery image`) on desktop, stacked on mobile.

---

### 6.5 `/donate` — Donation Page
**File:** [src/app/donate/page.tsx](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/donate/page.tsx)  
**Type:** Client Component  
**Purpose:** Displays UPI donation details (QR code, UPI ID, Account Name) dynamically fetched from the admin-configured database.

**Behavior:**
1. On mount, fetches `/api/get-settings` to retrieve live UPI configuration.
2. Fetches `/api/gallery-list` and picks one random image for the right panel.
3. Dynamically constructs a `upi://` deep link for mobile UPI apps.

**Layout:** Two-column (`2/3 donation block + 1/3 Cloudinary image`) on desktop, stacked on mobile.

**Conditional UI:**
- If `qrCode` is set: displays the QR image from Cloudinary.
- If not set: shows a dashed placeholder with instructional text.
- If `upiId` is set: renders UPI ID, Account Name, and "Pay with UPI" deep link button.
- If not set: shows placeholder text for each field.

