## 7. API Reference

All API routes are located in `src/app/api/`. They are **server-side Next.js Route Handlers**, communicating with Cloudinary and/or MongoDB. No authentication middleware is applied at the route level.

---

### `GET /api/gallery-list`
**File:** [src/app/api/gallery-list/route.ts](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/api/gallery-list/route.ts)  
**Purpose:** Retrieves all images in the Cloudinary `gallery/` folder.

**Cache:** `export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'` — fully bypasses Next.js cache; every request hits Cloudinary's API.

**Query Parameters:** None.

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "images": ["https://res.cloudinary.com/.../gallery/image1.jpg", "..."],
  "count": 42
}
```

**Error Response:** `{ "error": "Failed to fetch gallery" }` with status `500`.

**Cloudinary Call:** `cloudinary.api.resources()` with `prefix: 'gallery/'`, `max_results: 100`.

---

### `POST /api/gallery-upload`
**File:** [src/app/api/gallery-upload/route.ts](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/api/gallery-upload/route.ts)  
**Purpose:** Accepts multipart form data and uploads one or more images to Cloudinary under the `gallery/` folder.

**Request:** `multipart/form-data` with field name `files` (supports multiple files).

**Accepted Formats:** `jpg`, `jpeg`, `png`, `gif`, `webp`.

**Cloudinary Transformations on Upload:**
- `quality: 'auto:good'`
- `fetch_format: 'auto'` (serves WebP to supporting browsers)
- `width: 'auto', crop: 'scale'`

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "images": ["https://res.cloudinary.com/.../w_auto,q_auto,f_auto/gallery/..."],
  "count": 45
}
```

---

### `POST /api/gallery-delete`
**File:** `src/app/api/gallery-delete/route.ts`  
**Purpose:** Deletes one or more images from Cloudinary by their `secure_url`.

**Request Body:**
```json
{ "images": ["https://res.cloudinary.com/.../gallery/img1.jpg"] }
```

**Response:**
```json
{ "success": true }
```

---

### `POST /api/contact`
**File:** [src/app/api/contact/route.ts](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/api/contact/route.ts)  
**Purpose:** Receives contact form submissions and inserts them into MongoDB.

**Request Body:**
```json
{
  "fullName": "Ravi Sharma",
  "phoneNumber": "9876543210",
  "subject": "volunteer",
  "message": "I would like to volunteer..."
}
```

**Validation:** Checks all four fields are non-empty strings. No format validation (e.g., phone regex) is applied.

**MongoDB Write:** Inserts into `admin-panel` database, `contact_queries` collection with an additional `timestamp: new Date()` field.

**Response:** `{ "message": "Form data submitted successfully!" }` with status `200`.

---

### `GET /api/contact/queries`
**File:** `src/app/api/contact/queries/route.ts`  
**Purpose:** Returns all stored contact queries from MongoDB for admin review.

**Response:** Array of [ContactQuery](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/admin/page.tsx#16-24) objects.

**Access:** Unauthenticated — relies solely on URL obscurity.

---

### `DELETE /api/contact/queries/[id]`
**File:** `src/app/api/contact/queries/[id]/route.ts`  
**Purpose:** Deletes a contact query document from MongoDB by its `_id`.

**Access:** Unauthenticated — relies solely on URL obscurity.

---

### `GET /api/get-settings`
**File:** [src/app/api/get-settings/route.ts](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/api/get-settings/route.ts)  
**Purpose:** Retrieves the first settings document from the `settings` MongoDB collection.

**Response:** Settings object (or `defaultSettings` if none exist):
```json
{
  "upiId": "upihandle@bank",
  "upiName": "TheEducationForAll",
  "qrCode": "https://res.cloudinary.com/.../qr_code.png",
  "createdAt": "...",
  "updatedAt": "..."
}
```

---

### `POST /api/save-settings`
**File:** [src/app/api/save-settings/route.ts](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/api/save-settings/route.ts)  
**Purpose:** Creates or updates the settings document (upsert pattern) in MongoDB.

**Request Body:**
```json
{
  "upiId": "upihandle@bank",
  "upiName": "TheEducationForAll",
  "qrCode": "https://..."
}
```

**MongoDB Operation:** `updateOne({}, { $set: ... }, { upsert: true })` — always targets the first document.

---

### `POST /api/upload-qr`
**File:** `src/app/api/upload-qr/route.ts`  
**Purpose:** Uploads a QR code image to Cloudinary and returns its `secure_url`.

---

### `POST /api/remove-qr`
**File:** `src/app/api/remove-qr/route.ts`  
**Purpose:** Removes the QR code image from Cloudinary.

---

### `GET /api/test-cloudinary`
**File:** `src/app/api/test-cloudinary/route.ts`  
**Purpose:** Developer diagnostic endpoint. Tests Cloudinary connectivity and returns configuration status. Should be removed or protected before production deployment.

---

## 8. Data Models

### 8.1 Settings (MongoDB)
**Collection:** `settings` (in default database, determined by connection string)  
**File:** [src/models/Settings.ts](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/models/Settings.ts)

```typescript
interface Settings {
  _id?: ObjectId;      // Auto-generated by MongoDB
  upiId: string;       // e.g. "upihandle@bank"
  upiName: string;     // e.g. "TheEducationForAll"
  qrCode: string | null; // Cloudinary secure_url of the QR image, or null
  createdAt: Date;     // Set at creation/update time
  updatedAt: Date;     // Set at creation/update time
}
```

**Pattern:** Single-document settings store. Only one document is ever expected. The `updateOne({}, ..., { upsert: true })` pattern targets the first document found.

---

### 8.2 Contact Query (MongoDB)
**Collection:** `contact_queries` (in `admin-panel` database)  
**File:** Defined inline in [src/app/api/contact/route.ts](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/api/contact/route.ts) and typed in admin page.

```typescript
interface ContactQuery {
  _id: string;         // MongoDB ObjectId (serialised to string)
  fullName: string;
  phoneNumber: string;
  subject: string;     // One of: "general" | "volunteer" | "partnership" | "feedback"
  message: string;
  timestamp: Date;     // Set server-side at insert time
}
```

---

### 8.3 Cloudinary Gallery Images
Images are not stored in MongoDB. They live in the Cloudinary account under the `gallery/` folder. The database of record for gallery images is Cloudinary itself.

**URL Format:** `https://res.cloudinary.com/{cloud_name}/image/upload/{transformations}/gallery/{public_id}.{format}`

**Example transformation applied:** `/upload/w_200,q_30,f_auto/` (admin thumbnails), `/upload/w_auto,q_auto,f_auto/` (public-facing).

---

## 9. Component Library

The project has a single shared component in `src/components/`:

### [Navigation.tsx](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/components/Navigation.tsx)
**Type:** Client Component (`'use client'`)  
**Purpose:** Responsive top navigation bar, fixed, present on all pages.

**Props:** None. Reads `pathname` from `usePathname()`.

**Behavior:**
| Condition | Nav Background |
|---|---|
| On Home page (`/`), scroll position ≤ 50px | `transparent` |
| On Home page (`/`), scroll position > 50px | `bg-black` with shadow |
| On any other page | Always `bg-black` with shadow |

**Desktop Links:** Home, About Us, Gallery, Contact Us, Donate Now (styled as CTA button).

**Mobile:** A hamburger icon (SVG) opens a full-screen overlay with the same links. Overlay dismisses when a link is tapped.

**Note:** There is a duplicate scroll listener in [layout.tsx](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/layout.tsx) as a `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` script tag that targets a `#main-nav` ID. This ID does not exist in the rendered DOM (the `<nav>` in [Navigation.tsx](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/components/Navigation.tsx) has no ID). This script is effectively a dead code path.

---

## 10. Third-Party Service Integrations

### 10.1 MongoDB Atlas
**SDK:** `mongodb` (native Node.js driver)  
**File:** [src/lib/mongodb.ts](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/lib/mongodb.ts)

The connection is managed with a singleton pattern to handle Next.js's hot-reload behaviour in development (which would otherwise exhaust connection pool limits through repeated module evaluations):

```typescript
// In development: reuse connection stored on globalThis
if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development') {
  if (!global._mongoClientPromise) {
    client = new MongoClient(uri, { serverApi: ServerApiVersion.v1 });
    global._mongoClientPromise = client.connect();
  }
  clientPromise = global._mongoClientPromise;
} else {
  // In production: create a module-scoped promise
  client = new MongoClient(uri, { serverApi: ServerApiVersion.v1 });
  clientPromise = client.connect();
}
```

**Databases used:**
- `admin-panel`: Stores `contact_queries` collection.
- Default database (from URI): Stores `settings` collection.

**Note:** `export const db = client.db(process.env.MONGODB_DB)` at the bottom of [mongodb.ts](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/lib/mongodb.ts) references `client` before it is necessarily connected in all code paths (particularly the development branch where `global._mongoClientPromise` is used). This is a latent bug that may surface if `db` export is used before the promise resolves.

---

### 10.2 Cloudinary
**SDK:** `cloudinary` (v2 SDK, `v2 as cloudinary`)  
**File:** [src/lib/cloudinary.ts](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/lib/cloudinary.ts)

**Configured once** with `CLOUD_NAME`, `API_KEY`, and `API_SECRET`. Throws descriptive errors at module-load time if any variable is missing, which surfaces as a 500 error on the first API route that imports it.

**Note:** Several API routes (`gallery-upload`, `gallery-list`) also call `cloudinary.config()` redundantly. This has no side effects since re-configuring with the same values is idempotent, but creates code duplication.

**Folder structure in Cloudinary account:**
```
root/
└── gallery/       # All public event and field photographs
```
The QR code image is presumably uploaded to a separate path by `/api/upload-qr`.

---

### 10.3 Razorpay
The `razorpay` package (`^2.9.6`) is declared as a dependency in [package.json](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/package.json) but no `razorpay`-specific API routes or server-side Razorpay order creation has been found in the codebase. The current donation flow uses a pure UPI deep link (`upi://pay?pa=...`) rather than Razorpay's payment gateway. This package may be a planned future integration or a legacy artifact.

---

### 10.4 Next.js Image Optimisation
**Config file:** [next.config.js](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/next.config.js)

```js
images: {
  remotePatterns: [
    { protocol: 'https', hostname: 'picsum.photos' }
  ],
  domains: ['res.cloudinary.com'],  // DEPRECATED
}
```

The `images.domains` key is deprecated in Next.js 13+ and replaced by `images.remotePatterns`. The server emits a warning:
```
⚠ The "images.domains" configuration is deprecated. Please use "images.remotePatterns" configuration instead.
```

The `picsum.photos` hostname in `remotePatterns` appears unused in the current codebase.

---

## 11. Admin Panel

**Route:** `/admin`  
**File:** [src/app/admin/page.tsx](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/admin/page.tsx) (1,295 lines)  
**Type:** Client Component  
**Access Control:** Password-protected at client level only.

### 11.1 Authentication

```typescript
const ADMIN_PASSWORD = 'Feb@2020';
```

The admin password is **hardcoded directly in the client-side JavaScript bundle**. This means:
- Any visitor can view the password by inspecting the page source or the browser's built-in DevTools.
- Authentication state is stored in `sessionStorage` as `admin-auth: 'true'`, which is not cryptographically signed and can be set manually in the browser.

> [!CAUTION]
> This authentication scheme provides no real security. Anyone with browser DevTools access can bypass it. See Section 12 for remediation.

### 11.2 Dashboard Tabs

The admin UI uses a tab-based SPA layout with four sections:

| Tab | Icon | Content |
|---|---|---|
| Dashboard | FiHome | Overview — image count, loading status |
| Gallery | FiImage | Upload/delete/preview images |
| Queries | FiMessageSquare | View/delete contact form submissions |
| Settings | FiSettings | Configure UPI ID, account name, QR code |

Navigation is in a top bar on desktop and a fixed bottom bar on mobile.

### 11.3 Gallery Manager (Admin)
**Custom Hook:** [useGalleryManager()](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/admin/page.tsx#25-179)

**Features:**
- Fetches gallery with cache-busting: `?t=${Date.now()}`
- Auto-refreshes every 30 seconds via `setInterval`.
- **Upload:** Drag-and-drop or file picker (multi-file support). Simulates a 0–20% "preparing" progress, then begins actual upload. Shows status icons (spinner → checkmark/X).
- **Delete:** Checkbox multi-select of images. Confirmation dialog before deletion proceeds.
- **Image preview:** Clicking an image opens a full-size preview modal.
- Admin thumbnail optimisation: [getOptimizedImageUrl()](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/admin/page.tsx#9-14) transforms URLs to `w_200,q_30,f_auto` for fast admin panel rendering.

### 11.4 Contact Queries Manager (Admin)
**Custom Hook:** [useContactQueriesManager()](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/admin/page.tsx#180-234)

- Fetches all queries from `/api/contact/queries` on mount and every 30 seconds.
- Displays `fullName`, `phoneNumber`, `subject`, `message`, and `timestamp`.
- Delete button triggers a `confirm()` dialog, then calls `DELETE /api/contact/queries/[id]`.

### 11.5 Settings Panel (Admin)

- Form fields for UPI ID and UPI Name.
- QR code upload: File picker → POST to `/api/upload-qr` → stores returned URL via `/api/save-settings`.
- Remove QR: POST to `/api/remove-qr`, then clears from settings.
- Save Settings: POST to `/api/save-settings` with current UPI ID, name, and QR URL.

---

## 12. Security Considerations

| Risk | Severity | Detail |
|---|---|---|
| Hardcoded admin password in client JS | **Critical** | `ADMIN_PASSWORD = 'Feb@2020'` visible to anyone in DevTools. Must be replaced with server-side authentication (e.g., NextAuth.js or JWT cookie). |
| All admin API routes unprotected | **Critical** | `/api/contact/queries`, `/api/gallery-upload`, `/api/gallery-delete`, `/api/save-settings` are publicly accessible with no auth token requirement. A bad actor can delete all gallery images or dump all contact data. |
| `sessionStorage` auth token trivially forgeable | **High** | Setting `sessionStorage.setItem('admin-auth', 'true')` in DevTools grants full admin access. |
| No rate limiting on `/api/contact` | **Medium** | Allows unlimited spam form submissions, filling the MongoDB collection at no cost to the attacker. |
| No input sanitisation in `/api/contact` | **Medium** | Fields are stored raw. If rendered in admin without HTML escaping, stored XSS is possible. |
| `/api/test-cloudinary` publicly accessible | **Medium** | Exposes Cloudinary configuration status. Should be removed for production. |
| `images.domains` deprecation | **Low** | Deprecated config; does not represent a security issue but will break in a future Next.js major version. |
| Debug `console.log` statements in API routes | **Low** | `gallery-upload` and `gallery-list` log partial Cloudinary config (api key presence) to server logs. Should be removed in production. |

---

## 13. Known Issues & Recommendations

### Issue 1: Env file location mismatch
The original [.env](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/.env) file was placed in `d:/Education for All/web/` (parent directory) instead of `d:/Education for All/web/eduforall/` (Next.js root). This caused `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME` to not be loaded, resulting in a throw at `src/lib/cloudinary.ts:4`.

**Resolution:** A [.env.local](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/.env.local) file has been created in the correct project root.

### Issue 2: Dead `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` scroll script
[layout.tsx](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/layout.tsx) includes a `<script>` tag that manipulates `document.getElementById('main-nav')`. No element with `id="main-nav"` exists in the rendered DOM. This script is dead code.

**Recommendation:** Remove the `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` script block.

### Issue 3: Client-side gallery fetching causes CLS
Every page independently fetches the full list of up to 100 Cloudinary image URLs on mount, uses 1–3 of them, and discards the rest. This means:
- Each page load makes a fresh Cloudinary Admin API call.
- Images only appear after JavaScript runs (no SSR).
- Images/sections shift into place after initial render.

**Recommendation:** Convert image fetching to a Server Component or use Next.js ISR (`export const revalidate = 3600`) on the API route.

### Issue 4: [next.config.js](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/next.config.js) deprecation warning
`images.domains` is deprecated. Replace with `remotePatterns`.

### Issue 5: `db` export bug in [mongodb.ts](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/lib/mongodb.ts)
The `export const db = client.db(...)` at line 33 references the module-level `client` variable. In the development code path, `client` may be undefined if the global cache branch is taken. This export is currently unused but could cause runtime errors if imported.

### Issue 6: Admin polling every 30 seconds
Both [useGalleryManager](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/admin/page.tsx#25-179) and [useContactQueriesManager](file:///d:/Education%20for%20All/web/eduforall/src/app/admin/page.tsx#180-234) poll their respective APIs every 30 seconds via `setInterval`. If multiple admin browser tabs are open, this multiplies the load linearly.

**Recommendation:** Replace polling with manual "Refresh" button clicks or use SWR/React Query for smarter caching.

